7 Preamble
8 WHEREAS, The purpose of a cemetery is to be a permanent place for the disposition
9 of the dead, a sacred ground to memorialize and honor the dead, and to provide a place for
10 visitation by relatives, friends, and others to remember, honor, and grieve and to preserve
11 the history of those interred and their community; now, therefore,
12 BY repealing
13 Article – Business Regulation
14 Section 5–505
15 Annotated Code of Maryland
16 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
17 BY adding to
18 Article – Business Regulation
19 Section 5–505 and 5–507
