27 [5–506.
28 (a) An action may be brought in accordance with the Maryland Rules and a court
29 may pass a judgment for sale of a burial ground in Baltimore City for another purpose if:
30 (1) the ground has been dedicated and used for burial;

SENATE BILL 233 9
1 (2) burial lots have been sold in the burial ground and deeds executed or
2 other written instruments issued to buyers of the lots without provision being made for
3 perpetual care of the lots; and
4 (3) more than 75% of the area of the burial ground:
5 (i) has been abandoned; or
6 (ii) is harmful to the public health, safety, or welfare.
7 (b) The action may be brought by:
8 (1) a person with a property right in the burial ground; or
9 (2) a governmental unit with an interest in ending the conditions that are
10 harmful to the public health, safety, or welfare.
11 (c) If the court is satisfied that more than 75% of the area of a burial ground has
12 been abandoned or is harmful to the public health, safety, or welfare, the court:
13 (1) may pass a judgment for the sale of the entire burial ground on the
14 terms and notice the court sets; and
15 (2) may appoint a trustee to sell the burial ground.
16 (d) The trustee shall distribute the sale proceeds:
17 (1) first, to pay the expenses of removing any human remains, that, with
18 reasonable care, can be definitely located in the burial ground, buying burial lots in another
19 burial ground, and reburying the remains;
20 (2) second, to pay expenses of removing any markers that are in good
21 condition from the old lots and relocating the markers on new lots;
22 (3) third, to pay the expenses of ending conditions that are harmful to the
23 public health, safety, or welfare, unless the contract of sale of the burial ground provides
24 for abatement of those conditions within a reasonable period of time after the sale is
25 completed;
26 (4) fourth, to pay the costs of necessary legal proceedings, including court
27 costs, trustee’s commissions, and legal fees;
28 (5) fifth, to pay in full any taxes; and
29 (6) finally, to pay the balance of the proceeds to the person who,
30 immediately before the sale, had record title to the burial ground in its entirety according
31 to the land records of Baltimore City.

