17 (A) IN THIS SECTION, “CEMETERY OWNER” MEANS:
18 (1) A REGISTERED CEMETERIAN;
19 (2) A PERMIT HOLDER UNDER SUBTITLE 4 OF THIS TITLE; OR
20 (3) AN OWNER OF A CEMETERY THAT IS EXEMPT FROM THE
21 REGISTRATION AND PERMITTING REQUIREMENTS UNDER § 5–102 OF THIS TITLE.
22 (B) EXCEPT AS OTHERWISE PROVIDED IN SUBSECTIONS (G) AND (H) OF THIS
23 SECTION, THIS SECTION DOES NOT APPLY TO A RELIGIOUS ORGANIZATION THAT IS
24 A CEMETERY OWNER.
25 (C) (1) A REGISTERED CEMETERIAN OR PERMIT HOLDER MAY NOT SELL
26 OR TRANSFER A CEMETERY, IN WHOLE OR IN PART, TO ANOTHER PERSON FOR A USE
27 OTHER THAN AS A CEMETERY WITHOUT THE APPROVAL OF THE DIRECTOR.
28 (2) THE OWNER OF A CEMETERY THAT IS EXEMPT FROM THE
29 REGISTRATION AND PERMITTING REQUIREMENTS UNDER § 5–102 OF THIS TITLE

12 SENATE BILL 233
1 MAY NOT SELL OR TRANSFER THE CEMETERY, IN WHOLE OR IN PART, TO ANOTHER
2 PERSON WITHOUT THE APPROVAL OF THE DIRECTOR.
3 (D) BEFORE APPROVING THE SALE OR TRANSFER OF A CEMETERY UNDER
4 THIS SECTION, THE DIRECTOR SHALL:
5 (1) REQUIRE A CEMETERY OWNER TO SUBMIT TO THE DIRECTOR:
6 (I) AN APPLICATION UNDER SUBSECTION (E) OF THIS SECTION;
7 (II) A COMPLETED PRESERVATION PLAN UNDER SUBSECTION
8 (F) OF THIS SECTION; AND
9 (III) SATISFACTORY EVIDENCE OF COMPLETION OF THE PUBLIC
10 NOTICE REQUIREMENTS UNDER SUBSECTION (H) OF THIS SECTION; AND
11 (2) REVIEW AND CONSIDER ANY PUBLIC COMMENTS REGARDING THE
12 CEMETERY IN ACCORDANCE WITH SUBSECTION (I) OF THIS SECTION.
13 (E) (1) TO REQUEST APPROVAL TO SELL OR TRANSFER A CEMETERY
14 UNDER SUBSECTION (C) OF THIS SECTION, A CEMETERY OWNER SHALL SUBMIT AN
15 APPLICATION TO THE DIRECTOR ON THE FORM THAT THE DIRECTOR PROVIDES.
16 (2) IN ADDITION TO ANY OTHER INFORMATION REQUIRED ON AN
17 APPLICATION FORM, THE FORM SHALL REQUIRE:
18 (I) THE NAME AND ADDRESS OF EACH CEMETERY OWNER;
19 (II) NOTICE OF THE INTENT TO SELL OR TRANSFER THE
20 CEMETERY, IN WHOLE OR IN PART;
21 (III) A DESCRIPTION OF THE CEMETERY OR PART OF THE
22 CEMETERY INTENDED FOR SALE OR TRANSFER, INCLUDING THE NAME, LOCATION,
23 SIZE, ESTIMATED NUMBER OF HUMAN REMAINS AND PET REMAINS INTERRED IN THE
24 CEMETERY, AND NUMBER OF UNUSED OR UNSOLD BURIAL SITES;
25 (IV) THE NAME AND CONTACT INFORMATION OF ANY POTENTIAL
26 BUYERS OR TRANSFEREES OF THE CEMETERY, IF KNOWN;
27 (V) AN AGREEMENT TO SUBMIT A PRESERVATION PLAN IN
28 ACCORDANCE WITH SUBSECTION (F) OF THIS SECTION; AND
29 (VI) A COPY OF THE PUBLIC NOTICE REQUIRED UNDER
30 SUBSECTION (H) OF THIS SECTION.

