22 (II) PLACING A WRITTEN NOTICE OF INTENT TO SELL OR
23 TRANSFER IN THE CEMETERY AT A CONSPICUOUS LOCATION IN FULL PUBLIC VIEW
24 FOR NOT LESS THAN 60 DAYS;
25 (III) PROVIDING NOTICE TO LOCAL GENEALOGICAL AND
26 HISTORICAL SOCIETIES; AND
27 (IV) HOLDING A PUBLIC MEETING AT WHICH PUBLIC TESTIMONY
28 MUST BE OFFERED.
29 (2) A PUBLIC NOTICE REQUIRED UNDER PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS
30 SUBSECTION SHALL INCLUDE:
31 (I) THE ADDRESS OF THE CEMETERY;

14 SENATE BILL 233
1 (II) THE ESTIMATED SIZE AND NUMBER OF HUMAN REMAINS OR
2 PET REMAINS INTERRED IN THE CEMETERY;
3 (III) ANY AVAILABLE INFORMATION ABOUT THE CEMETERY
4 FROM THE STATE DEPARTMENT OF ASSESSMENTS AND TAXATION; AND
