6 THE CEMETERY.
7 (I) BEFORE APPROVING THE SALE OR TRANSFER OF A CEMETERY UNDER
8 THIS SECTION, THE DIRECTOR SHALL CONSIDER ANY PUBLIC COMMENTS ABOUT
9 THE CEMETERY RECEIVED BY THE CEMETERY OWNER AT A PUBLIC HEARING UNDER
10 SUBSECTION (H)(1)(IV) OF THIS SECTION OR BY THE DIRECTOR, INCLUDING:
11 (1) WHETHER THE CEMETERY OWNER HAS CONSIDERED THE
12 CONCERNS OF THE DESCENDANT COMMUNITY, INCLUDING:
13 (I) REASONS FOR THE PROPOSED SALE OR TRANSFER AND
14 FUTURE PLANS FOR THE PROPERTY;
15 (II) WHETHER THE CURRENT LOCATION OF THE CEMETERY
16 HOLDS ANY CULTURAL OR HISTORICAL SIGNIFICANCE;
17 (III) THE COST OF DISINTERMENT AND REINTERMENT OF THE
18 HUMAN REMAINS OR PET REMAINS IN THE CEMETERY AND WHO SHOULD BEAR THE
19 COST; AND
20 (IV) WHERE ANY HUMAN REMAINS OR PET REMAINS
21 DISINTERRED FROM THE CEMETERY WOULD BE RELOCATED; AND
22 (2) WHETHER THE CEMETERY OWNER RECEIVED OTHER EQUIVALENT
23 OFFERS FOR PURCHASE OF THE CEMETERY THAT MAY BE LESS DISRUPTIVE TO THE
24 CEMETERY.
25 (J) THE DIRECTOR SHALL APPROVE THE SALE OR TRANSFER OF A
26 CEMETERY OR PART OF A CEMETERY UNDER THIS SECTION IF:
27 (1) THE CEMETERY OWNER SATISFIES ALL THE REQUIREMENTS OF
28 THIS SECTION; AND
29 (2) THE DIRECTOR DETERMINES THAT IT IS IN THE INTEREST OF ALL
30 THE PARTIES TO SELL OR TRANSFER THE CEMETERY OR PART OF THE CEMETERY.

